1
00:00:09,810 --> 00:00:11,020
Hey.

2
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:12,990
It's about time to get ready.

3
00:00:13,790 --> 00:00:16,120
Yeah, I'm up.

4
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:18,690
You've said that three times already.

5
00:00:30,910 --> 00:00:32,320
Are you that excited?

6
00:00:35,030 --> 00:00:36,440
Of course.

7
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:39,850
It's our first trip together, after all.

8
00:00:41,490 --> 00:00:43,020
What about the school trip?

9
00:00:43,870 --> 00:00:45,960
That was ages ago.

10
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:48,310
Honestly,

11
00:00:48,740 --> 00:00:50,420
you probably don't understand

12
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:52,080
how much I was looking forward

13
00:00:53,170 --> 00:00:54,730
to this trip.

14
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,140
I understand.

15
00:00:57,950 --> 00:00:59,770
I was looking forward to it too.

16
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:02,440
Really?

17
00:01:11,660 --> 00:01:17,370
[JP Minakami Station]

18
00:01:17,420 --> 00:01:21,320
[Special Episode:
What Would've Become of Us?]

19
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:19,490
Ah.

20
00:01:20,780 --> 00:01:22,670
Wow.

21
00:01:25,950 --> 00:01:28,830
[Steamed Bun]

22
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:32,930
You're eating it already?

23
00:01:32,930 --> 00:01:35,370
You like it, right?

24
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:33,230
I'll just leave the tea here.

25
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:34,150
Mm.

26
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:35,860
Thanks.

27
00:02:43,050 --> 00:02:44,850
Ah.

28
00:02:46,990 --> 00:02:50,020
It's been so long
since I've gone on a trip.

29
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,950
You used to travel a lot in college,
didn't you?

30
00:02:52,950 --> 00:02:54,050
Yeah.

31
00:02:54,430 --> 00:02:55,829
Did Futami tell you that?

32
00:02:56,660 --> 00:02:57,180
Sort of.

33
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:03,140
He didn't say anything weird, did he?

34
00:03:03,490 --> 00:03:05,070
Got something to hide?

35
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:06,990
No, nothing at all.

36
00:03:09,390 --> 00:03:12,220
Something like a casual trip
between friends.

37
00:03:12,660 --> 00:03:14,610
But actually,
you're hitting on each other.

38
00:03:14,610 --> 00:03:15,490
Eh?

39
00:03:16,210 --> 00:03:18,730
You're just too good at everything,

40
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:20,280
like making arrangements.

41
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:23,000
I'm not that good at it.

42
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:24,400
You really are,

43
00:03:24,890 --> 00:03:27,690
whether it's flirting with others
or holding men.

44
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:32,100
You said before
that it's easier with guys.

45
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,780
That was...

46
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:36,600
I just said that at that time.
It wasn't actually true.

47
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,460
But it wasn't a lie either, right?

48
00:03:40,210 --> 00:03:41,460
Once,

49
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,329
I wanted to forget you.

50
00:03:45,570 --> 00:03:48,210
There was a time
when I was kind of self-destructive.

51
00:03:48,210 --> 00:03:48,910
Eh?

52
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:51,980
After high school graduation,

53
00:03:52,570 --> 00:03:55,100
I decided to let you go.

54
00:03:57,470 --> 00:04:00,070
But no matter what,
I just couldn't forget you.

55
00:04:00,970 --> 00:04:02,390
If that's how it was,

56
00:04:02,420 --> 00:04:04,350
why didn't you just reach out to me?

57
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:07,080
I wanted to put a proper end
to things too.

58
00:04:07,310 --> 00:04:08,810
Reaching a conclusion on your own

59
00:04:08,810 --> 00:04:10,400
is your bad habit.

60
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:15,390
But since I pushed you
to that self-destructive state,

61
00:04:15,810 --> 00:04:16,920
I'll forgive you.

62
00:04:21,279 --> 00:04:22,340
If...

63
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:26,770
we had stayed in touch
after high school graudation,

64
00:04:28,570 --> 00:04:29,880
what would've become

65
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:31,160
of us?

66
00:04:31,530 --> 00:04:32,220
Who knows?

67
00:04:36,670 --> 00:04:37,770
Zen,

68
00:04:39,090 --> 00:04:40,680
after you started college,

69
00:04:41,140 --> 00:04:43,340
did you ever think about contacting me?

70
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,150
Well...

71
00:04:46,340 --> 00:04:47,940
I might have been waiting...

72
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,320
for you to contact me.

73
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,650
Eh? You're lying, right?

74
00:04:52,650 --> 00:04:53,659
Because

75
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,700
you looked like
you had no interest in me at all.

76
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:57,800
That's pretty rude.

77
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:00,950
-Look, you're blushing.
-Did you even listen to what I just said?

78
00:05:00,950 --> 00:05:03,530
Don't make assumptions
about how I feel on your own.

79
00:05:03,530 --> 00:05:05,040
-Mr. Self-Ending.
-Hah?

80
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:09,980
Why are you only saying all this now?

81
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:11,470
Because you asked.

82
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,130
Then,

83
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:16,220
if we had contacted each other earlier,

84
00:05:16,220 --> 00:05:17,280
could we have

85
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:19,640
become like this sooner?

86
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:26,320
Eh...

87
00:05:28,630 --> 00:05:30,880
I wish I could go back in time.

88
00:05:31,450 --> 00:05:33,710
We can just make up for lost time instead.

89
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:36,030
We've got so many more years ahead

90
00:05:37,159 --> 00:05:38,220
to spend together.

91
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:43,510
True.

92
00:05:46,690 --> 00:05:52,730
[Public Bath
Meigetsu Hot Spring]

93
00:05:48,659 --> 00:05:51,300
Ah, so comfortable.

94
00:05:51,330 --> 00:05:54,320
This is great.

95
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,710
Cheers.

96
00:06:39,620 --> 00:06:40,840
Ah, this is good.

97
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:45,190
Mmm, this is tasty.

98
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:51,409
Put the vegetables in.

99
00:06:51,430 --> 00:06:52,540
Eh.

100
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:56,570
Hehe.

101
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:58,930
Is it good?

102
00:06:58,960 --> 00:06:59,550
Yeah.

103
00:07:00,230 --> 00:07:01,500
Let me try this too.

104
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,170
It's good, right?

105
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:17,880
Ah, it's so delicious.

106
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:22,610
The first thing on my list
of things to do with Zen

107
00:07:22,970 --> 00:07:24,610
has been done.

108
00:07:25,450 --> 00:07:26,390
What?

109
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:28,140
How many things are on it?

110
00:07:28,140 --> 00:07:30,040
Ah, there are a lot.

111
00:07:32,210 --> 00:07:34,800
Watching a movie, going for a night drive,

112
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:36,390
camping,

113
00:07:36,710 --> 00:07:38,570
fishing, and traveling abroad.

114
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,780
I forgot

115
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:43,520
that our interests don't really match.

116
00:07:43,730 --> 00:07:45,600
You've always been a homebody.

117
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:49,090
I really should build up some stamina.

118
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,840
I've never won on anything athletic.

119
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:53,050
Just to win?

120
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,680
It's to keep you company.

121
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:04,560
Hey.

122
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:06,620
Slow down with the drinks.

123
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,730
I'll be upset if you pass out first.

124
00:08:08,990 --> 00:08:11,990
You weren't planning
to let me sleep anyway, were you?

125
00:08:12,590 --> 00:08:13,650
You read me so well.

126
00:08:14,070 --> 00:08:15,670
You're just too easy to read.

127
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:17,390
Then,

128
00:08:18,510 --> 00:08:19,810
what do I want to do now?

129
00:08:20,450 --> 00:08:21,180
Take a guess.

130
00:08:24,330 --> 00:08:25,060
That's...

131
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:33,750
Here you are.

132
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:37,140
It's a bit early, but...

133
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,400
Happy birthday.

134
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,320
Thank you.

135
00:08:42,570 --> 00:08:43,409
Hmm?

136
00:08:44,570 --> 00:08:46,210
Were you expecting anything else?

137
00:08:46,210 --> 00:08:47,250
Not at all.

138
00:08:48,090 --> 00:08:48,830
Can I open it?

139
00:08:48,860 --> 00:08:49,680
Go ahead.

140
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:03,390
I wanted to give you something
you can carry with you,

141
00:09:03,390 --> 00:09:04,440
so it's a bit

142
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,900
too ordinary.

143
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,070
Because it's you,

144
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:10,310
I thought you'd prepare a ring.

145
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:13,230
Then I'll go get mine too.

146
00:09:13,890 --> 00:09:14,600
Okay.

147
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:16,730
You probably know what it is.

148
00:09:19,170 --> 00:09:21,250
I should have bought a ring.

149
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:23,480
Here you are.

150
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:29,460
Once again,

151
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:31,380
thank you.

152
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,200
I went through so much trouble

153
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,970
just to get you this gift.

154
00:09:36,950 --> 00:09:38,260
Sorry.

155
00:09:38,830 --> 00:09:40,640
Can I open it?

156
00:09:40,670 --> 00:09:41,740
Open it later.

157
00:09:43,460 --> 00:09:44,660
If you don't hurry up,

158
00:09:45,050 --> 00:09:46,510
I'm really going to sleep.

159
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:49,030
What?

160
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:51,210
You're so eager.

161
00:09:51,820 --> 00:09:54,350
Don't think
you're the only one holding back.

162
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:57,570
Ryo.

163
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,450
Happy birthday.

164
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:07,480
Thank you.

165
00:10:15,230 --> 00:10:16,420
Who is it?

166
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:18,810
At this time on Saturday?

167
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,860
It's Futami.

168
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,560
Can I ignore it?

169
00:10:27,090 --> 00:10:27,830
Don't.

170
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,720
It's been ringing
since last night, hasn't it?

171
00:10:31,410 --> 00:10:34,150
After all, we parted like that.

172
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:35,620
Ryo

173
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:38,340
is my lover.

174
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:48,290
You should give him a call.

175
00:10:48,970 --> 00:10:51,630
It's more annoying
to be disturbed repeatedly.

176
00:10:52,770 --> 00:10:54,210
True.

177
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:55,990
Ah, you finally answered.

178
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:56,610
Wait a minute.

179
00:10:56,610 --> 00:10:57,460
Hello.

180
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:59,110
Why didn't you tell me you were dating?

181
00:10:59,110 --> 00:11:00,490
Sorry.

182
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:01,920
How should I put it?

183
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,810
Let me get my revenge.

184
00:12:22,550 --> 00:12:24,160
I knew you would say that.

185
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,360
So, what is the rule?

186
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:29,190
Whoever caves first loses.

187
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:32,090
As always,

188
00:12:32,110 --> 00:12:33,990
it's such a dumb contest.

189
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,180
Yeah.

190
00:12:36,590 --> 00:12:38,610
Being with you makes me dumber.

191
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,450
It's too late to turn back now, isn't it?

192
00:12:44,450 --> 00:12:46,850
Guess I've got no choice but to give up.

193
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:19,990
Your yukata looks amazing.

194
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:22,240
Yours too.

195
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:56,820
I feel totally refreshed.

196
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,740
I won the contest.

197
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:01,760
Alright, alright.

198
00:14:01,790 --> 00:14:02,790
I got it.

199
00:14:03,520 --> 00:14:04,290
So,

200
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:06,200
what do you want me to do?

201
00:14:07,340 --> 00:14:08,310
Well...

202
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:16,050
Let's move in together.

203
00:14:18,430 --> 00:14:19,120
Eh?

204
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,420
The winner gets to call the shots, right?

205
00:14:22,530 --> 00:14:22,960
Huh?

206
00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:26,080
Wait a minute. Um...

207
00:14:26,810 --> 00:14:28,650
Does that mean us living together?

208
00:14:28,650 --> 00:14:29,180
Yeah.

209
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:32,270
Staying at one of our places temporarily.

210
00:14:32,290 --> 00:14:34,030
Ah, wait, wait.

211
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:36,920
Well...

212
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:38,420
Why so sudden?

213
00:14:38,450 --> 00:14:39,450
It's not sudden.

214
00:14:40,030 --> 00:14:42,230
I've been thinking about it for a while.

215
00:14:42,990 --> 00:14:45,800
I don't want to be apart from you,
and I don't want to miss you again.

216
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:46,940
I want

217
00:14:47,580 --> 00:14:49,110
to spend more time with you.

218
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:51,190
Zen.

219
00:14:52,670 --> 00:14:54,370
Are you serious?

220
00:14:54,790 --> 00:14:56,670
How could I possibly be joking?

221
00:14:59,270 --> 00:15:00,250
What about you?

222
00:15:02,190 --> 00:15:03,390
Of course,

223
00:15:05,060 --> 00:15:07,000
I definitely want to.

224
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:10,140
Really?

225
00:15:10,170 --> 00:15:10,800
This is the best

226
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,010
surprise gift.

227
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,290
You're overreacting.

228
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:16,280
I've got leverage now.

229
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:17,320
Now,

230
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:19,210
you can't take back what you said.

231
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:21,290
That's against the rule.

232
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:23,380
Don't add a new rule on your own.

233
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:25,380
Be prepared.

234
00:15:25,930 --> 00:15:27,790
My love is pretty heavy, you know.

235
00:15:27,810 --> 00:15:28,970
Maybe it is, for now.

236
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:30,990
But

237
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,820
I'll catch up soon enough anyway.

238
00:15:47,210 --> 00:15:49,260
I'll get in touch with the client then.

239
00:15:49,260 --> 00:15:50,340
Thank you.

240
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,290
I'll leave the scheduling to you.

241
00:15:52,310 --> 00:15:53,010
Okay.

242
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:54,070
Yoshii.

243
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:54,960
Make copies of this.

244
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:55,640
Okay.

245
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:13,190
I've sorted out all the client data files.

246
00:16:13,220 --> 00:16:14,460
Let's split up the work.

247
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:14,990
-Okay.
-Got it.

248
00:16:14,990 --> 00:16:16,640
-Let's get started.
-Ah, Mr. Minami.

249
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,490
Please back up Onishi and Higashino.

250
00:16:18,490 --> 00:16:19,480
Got it.

251
00:16:46,650 --> 00:16:47,880
Do you come shopping here?

252
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:49,720
No, not really.

253
00:16:49,740 --> 00:16:51,350
You don't?

254
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:57,430
I told you it's too flashy.

255
00:16:57,430 --> 00:16:58,730
Oh, how cute.

256
00:16:59,530 --> 00:17:00,600
It looks weird, right?

257
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:03,210
This one is cute too.

258
00:17:12,589 --> 00:17:13,960
-Delicious.
-Hahaha.

259
00:17:34,740 --> 00:17:36,070
Well, everyone,

260
00:17:36,590 --> 00:17:38,390
thanks for your hard work again.

261
00:17:39,050 --> 00:17:39,780
Cheers!

262
00:17:40,170 --> 00:17:43,670
-Thanks.
-Thanks.

263
00:17:43,690 --> 00:17:44,880
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

264
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,580
-Thanks.
-Thanks.

265
00:17:46,610 --> 00:17:48,240
-Thanks.
-Thanks.

266
00:17:48,260 --> 00:17:49,630
-Thanks.
-Thanks.

267
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:54,610
Ah.

268
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,990
Ah, what a rough ride.

269
00:17:57,010 --> 00:17:58,540
I thought I was going to die.

270
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:01,090
Honestly, the past two weeks
feel like a total blur.

271
00:18:01,090 --> 00:18:03,660
It's rare that the entire Sales Department
is on one project.

272
00:18:03,660 --> 00:18:05,030
Glad it ended well.

273
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:06,730
And right in the middle of all this,

274
00:18:06,730 --> 00:18:09,210
my sister had her wedding.

275
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:10,070
Oh, that really...

276
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:11,530
That must have been tough.

277
00:18:12,260 --> 00:18:16,370
I was called in to help
when we were so busy.

278
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:17,490
But

279
00:18:17,510 --> 00:18:20,710
I still got really moved
when I was actually at the wedding.

280
00:18:20,710 --> 00:18:21,830
What about you, Mr. Yotsuya?

281
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:22,570
Ah?

282
00:18:22,610 --> 00:18:23,110
Oh.

283
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:24,140
With your girlfriend.

284
00:18:24,140 --> 00:18:25,890
Yeah, any plans to get married?

285
00:18:25,910 --> 00:18:26,900
Yeah.

286
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:30,440
Same goes for you, Mr. Shido. You already
live together with your girlfriend.

287
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:31,270
No...

288
00:18:32,110 --> 00:18:33,210
Mm.

289
00:18:33,670 --> 00:18:35,540
I have been thinking about it.

290
00:18:36,130 --> 00:18:38,110
-Ooh!
-Ooh!

291
00:18:38,140 --> 00:18:38,600
Eh?

292
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:39,570
What about you, Mr. Shido?

293
00:18:39,570 --> 00:18:40,130
Indeed.

294
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:42,050
-Wait.
-Mm.

295
00:18:42,070 --> 00:18:45,400
Marriage isn't something
you can take lightly.

296
00:18:45,420 --> 00:18:46,020
Exactly.

297
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:47,470
It takes a lot of time to prepare.

298
00:18:47,470 --> 00:18:49,100
Of course I'm thinking about it.

299
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,380
Ooh!

300
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:52,530
I,

301
00:18:53,410 --> 00:18:55,810
from the moment
we decided to date each other,

302
00:18:55,810 --> 00:18:57,410
was already prepared for it.

303
00:18:58,310 --> 00:19:02,470
-Wow!
-Wow!

304
00:19:02,490 --> 00:19:04,190
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

305
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:07,140
What's with that look?

306
00:19:07,170 --> 00:19:07,890
Ha.

307
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:10,040
Alright, tell me

308
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:11,250
what

309
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:13,740
each of you like about your partners.

310
00:19:13,970 --> 00:19:14,970
Spare no details.

311
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:17,420
Well,

312
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,120
lots of things.

313
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:22,360
Pretty much everything.

314
00:19:23,420 --> 00:19:24,990
Whoo-hoo!

315
00:19:25,020 --> 00:19:26,550
It's about time
you showed us some photos, right?

316
00:19:26,550 --> 00:19:27,200
Come on, show us.

317
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:29,100
And Mr. Shido, say something.

318
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:30,070
Like I'd ever say anything.

319
00:19:30,070 --> 00:19:31,270
Come on, please.

320
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:32,030
Not a chance.

321
00:19:32,060 --> 00:19:33,890
What's with that look?

322
00:19:33,910 --> 00:19:34,920
Jealous?

323
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:36,630
What's there to be jealous of?

324
00:19:36,990 --> 00:19:39,010
-Haha.
-So jealous.

325
00:19:40,410 --> 00:19:42,860
You're keeping us at arm's length.

326
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:43,710
What?

327
00:19:43,740 --> 00:19:44,950
See?

328
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,080
Come on, don't just talk.

329
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:50,810
I'm not like you.

330
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,740
-Ooh!
-Hahahaha.

331
00:19:52,770 --> 00:19:55,370
Nishijima,
why do you keep talking about this?

332
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:12,620
You were going on and on with a huge smile

333
00:20:12,910 --> 00:20:14,240
about your girlfriend.

334
00:20:14,770 --> 00:20:16,020
Sorry.

335
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,340
Got a bit carried away.

336
00:20:19,210 --> 00:20:20,030
And then?

337
00:20:21,250 --> 00:20:23,220
Marriage and stuff.

338
00:20:23,940 --> 00:20:25,940
I don't remember being proposed to.

339
00:20:26,630 --> 00:20:27,360
That's...

340
00:20:30,150 --> 00:20:32,210
But I am seriously thinking about it.

341
00:20:33,180 --> 00:20:34,250
Humph.

342
00:20:36,420 --> 00:20:37,620
Zen.

343
00:20:38,980 --> 00:20:41,440
You always think carefully
about our future

344
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:43,900
and then tell me about it.

345
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:45,820
Yeah.

346
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:46,620
Mhm.

347
00:20:49,810 --> 00:20:51,420
Since we started dating,

348
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:53,800
you have been prepared.

349
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:54,970
When you said that,

350
00:20:56,060 --> 00:20:57,430
you were super cool.

351
00:20:59,570 --> 00:21:01,590
I really like that about you.

352
00:21:06,330 --> 00:21:08,620
But if I'm allowed to be a little greedy,

353
00:21:10,760 --> 00:21:13,220
I still want to know
what you like about me.

354
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,880
We should talk about that
when we're alone.

355
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:21,570
Our sales results were tied
this quarter, right?

356
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:22,880
Huh?

357
00:21:23,300 --> 00:21:24,080
Actually,

358
00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:26,590
I want you to tell me

359
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:29,420
ten things you like about me.

360
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:34,080
Try again next year.

361
00:21:35,610 --> 00:21:36,290
Good luck.

362
00:21:37,620 --> 00:21:38,860
I'll do my best.

363
00:21:40,310 --> 00:21:42,640
I'd be troubled
if you said you were bored.

364
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:45,080
You're still holding a grudge?

365
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:46,340
Because...

366
00:21:46,690 --> 00:21:47,630
I want to...

367
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,110
always...

368
00:21:49,130 --> 00:21:51,150
be your rival.

369
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:54,420
Don't worry about that.

370
00:21:56,610 --> 00:21:58,870
We're not just ordinary rivals anymore.

371
00:22:07,140 --> 00:22:09,200
The way you never compromise at work.

372
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:11,260
Hm?

373
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,040
What?

374
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:14,800
Since it was a tie,

375
00:22:15,750 --> 00:22:16,900
let's do half. Five.

376
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,320
Five things I like about you.

377
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:26,340
You say some too.

378
00:22:30,580 --> 00:22:32,710
The way you get unexpectedly jealous.

379
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:33,280
Huh?

380
00:22:35,650 --> 00:22:37,850
The way you're not cute at all
when you're jealous.

381
00:22:37,850 --> 00:22:40,220
The way you get competitive
over everything.

382
00:22:40,220 --> 00:22:41,650
The way you hate losing.

383
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:42,950
You too.

384
00:22:46,730 --> 00:22:47,430
Next.

385
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:53,770
When I'm with you,

386
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:58,340
I feel like everything will be fine
no matter what happens.

387
00:23:03,530 --> 00:23:05,790
The way you love me so deeply.

388
00:23:07,730 --> 00:23:08,600
Okay, I'm out of words.

389
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:09,010
Done.

390
00:23:09,030 --> 00:23:10,430
Only four?

391
00:23:10,450 --> 00:23:11,730
No, I can't think of any more.

392
00:23:11,730 --> 00:23:12,230
No way.

393
00:23:12,260 --> 00:23:13,400
There's got to be at least one more.

394
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:14,040
Have you thought of one?

395
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:15,560
-I have.
-You...

396
00:23:15,780 --> 00:23:17,370
Hahaha, seriously.

397
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:20,790
I never imagined

398
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,800
that after becoming lovers,

399
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:26,280
we could say things we like

400
00:23:28,070 --> 00:23:29,600
about each other like this.

401
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,810
The way we started was just terrible.

402
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:36,380
Sorry.

403
00:23:38,290 --> 00:23:38,980
But,

404
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:41,930
regardless of our relationship,

405
00:23:43,110 --> 00:23:44,680
ever since high school,

406
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:48,520
I've always been the happiest
when I'm with you.

407
00:23:50,730 --> 00:23:51,360
I...

408
00:23:54,190 --> 00:23:56,750
love the version of myself
when I'm with you...

409
00:23:56,750 --> 00:23:57,830
the most.

410
00:24:02,890 --> 00:24:03,730
Then,

411
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:05,840
that's the fifth one.

412
00:24:12,890 --> 00:24:13,750
You...

413
00:24:14,590 --> 00:24:17,920
What are you doing all of a sudden?
We're outside, you idiot.

414
00:24:20,210 --> 00:24:21,820
I guess I'm an idiot.

415
00:24:31,190 --> 00:24:32,330
I,

416
00:24:34,910 --> 00:24:36,690
ever since we started dating,

417
00:24:41,850 --> 00:24:43,850
have always felt like I'm dreaming.

418
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:50,830
Then,

419
00:24:52,930 --> 00:24:53,730
from now on,

420
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:55,750
we'll have to make it a reality.

421
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:13,660
Are you cold?

422
00:25:17,540 --> 00:25:18,580
I'm fine.

423
00:25:20,270 --> 00:25:21,860
You body is warm.

424
00:25:35,910 --> 00:25:37,210
What's this?

425
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:41,480
I like you.

426
00:25:49,350 --> 00:25:51,170
What's with that look?

427
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,900
You really like me, don't you?

428
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:05,780
Saying "like" isn't enough anymore.

429
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:13,410
I love you.

430
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:16,300
Always.

431
00:26:19,110 --> 00:26:20,370
For the rest of my life.

432
00:26:22,230 --> 00:26:23,450
That's heavy.

433
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:26,860
But you'll accept it, right?

434
00:26:29,630 --> 00:26:30,500
Of course.

435
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:44,510
-3, 2, 1.
-Eh?

436
00:26:51,120 --> 00:26:53,110
What are you doing?

437
00:26:53,580 --> 00:26:55,180
What about you? What's that?

438
00:26:55,220 --> 00:26:56,220
What?

439
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:57,240
What do you think?

440
00:26:57,890 --> 00:26:59,290
It's for a proposal.

441
00:27:00,770 --> 00:27:02,590
A ring. We got the same thing.

442
00:27:07,270 --> 00:27:10,240
Why did we prepare the same thing
at the same time?

443
00:27:10,270 --> 00:27:11,060
No.

444
00:27:11,090 --> 00:27:12,850
I've had this ready for a long time.

445
00:27:12,850 --> 00:27:14,030
Me too.

446
00:27:14,180 --> 00:27:16,150
Then why now?

447
00:27:16,330 --> 00:27:17,780
It's not even a special day.

448
00:27:17,780 --> 00:27:19,690
Precisely because it's not a special day,

449
00:27:19,690 --> 00:27:21,130
this is a surprise.

450
00:27:23,110 --> 00:27:24,120
Ahaha.

451
00:27:26,490 --> 00:27:27,840
Not cool at all.

452
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:29,660
But,

453
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:33,130
it feels like something
the two of us would do.

454
00:27:39,770 --> 00:27:40,510
Zen.

455
00:27:41,130 --> 00:27:42,310
Give me your hand.

456
00:27:56,700 --> 00:27:58,720
From now on, let's keep

457
00:28:01,660 --> 00:28:03,300
having our silly contests.

458
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:07,090
What a weird proposal.

459
00:28:08,370 --> 00:28:10,050
This feels more like something we'd do,

460
00:28:10,050 --> 00:28:11,250
if it suits us better.

461
00:28:13,510 --> 00:28:15,010
Zen, before,

462
00:28:15,750 --> 00:28:18,080
didn't you say you wanted
to make me happy?

463
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:20,830
But,

464
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:25,050
I want us to be happy together.

465
00:28:25,390 --> 00:28:26,510
We're already...

466
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:29,870
doing that now, aren't we?

467
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:44,080
To become a man worthy
of being my partner,

468
00:28:44,110 --> 00:28:46,210
please work hard.

469
00:28:47,500 --> 00:28:49,050
You too.

470
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:19,430
I won this quarter.

471
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:23,520
What's wrong?

472
00:29:23,910 --> 00:29:26,490
Pulling a long face. That's not like you.

473
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:28,090
As always,

474
00:29:28,380 --> 00:29:30,490
you're so smug.

475
00:29:30,940 --> 00:29:31,710
Huh?

476
00:29:31,740 --> 00:29:33,170
Shouldn't I be smug?

477
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:34,980
You're definitely comparing profits again,
aren't you?

478
00:29:34,980 --> 00:29:36,380
Well, the profits are...

479
00:29:37,420 --> 00:29:38,670
I feel like

480
00:29:38,770 --> 00:29:40,900
this has become a very familiar scene.

481
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:41,740
Yeah.

482
00:29:42,610 --> 00:29:43,610
But

483
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:44,900
compared to before...

484
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:47,230
What's wrong with those two?

485
00:29:47,250 --> 00:29:48,750
Are they arguing again?

486
00:29:48,780 --> 00:29:49,350
Yes.

487
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:51,180
Even if they each

488
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:54,260
got married, they'd still be like this,
wouldn't they?

489
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:56,320
Who knows?

490
00:29:58,350 --> 00:29:59,240
You two,

491
00:29:59,730 --> 00:30:01,330
help me prepare for the meeting.

492
00:30:01,330 --> 00:30:02,180
-Okay.
-Okay.

493
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:08,190
You need to finish

494
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:12,150
the remaining five tonight.

495
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:14,030
Yeah.

496
00:30:14,530 --> 00:30:16,040
The winner

497
00:30:16,420 --> 00:30:17,660
calls all the shots.

498
00:30:24,980 --> 00:30:31,990
[Fake Fact Lips]
